af.latex:
In die volgende lys is daar een onware verklaring en twee ware stellings.
Watter stellings is waar?
1. Elke heelgetal is 'n natuurlike getal.
2. Elke natuurlike getal is 'n telgetal.
3. Daar is geen desimale in telgetalle nie.
af.html:
In die volgende lys is daar een onware verklaring en twee ware stellings.
Watter stellings is waar?
1. Elke heelgetal is 'n natuurlike getal.
2. Elke natuurlike getal is 'n telgetal.
3. Daar is geen desimale in telgetalle nie.

en.latex:
Consider each option carefully:
1. There are integers which do not fall into the natural numbers (all negative numbers), so this is false.
2. The natural numbers are \( {1;2;3;\ldots} \) and whole numbers are \( {0;1;2;3; \ldots } \) (the circle \( \mathbb{N} \) is inside \( \mathbb{N}_0 \) ) so if a number is a natural number it must be a whole number.
This is true.
3. Whole numbers \( {0;1;2;3;\ldots} \) only go up in steps of 1, so there cannot be any decimal numbers in the whole numbers, making this true.
Therefore \( (2) \) and \( (3) \) is true.
en.html:
Consider each option carefully:
1. There are integers which do not fall into the natural numbers (all negative numbers), so this is false.
2. The natural numbers are \( {1;2;3;\ldots} \) and whole numbers are \( {0;1;2;3; \ldots } \) (the circle \( \mathbb{N} \) is inside \( \mathbb{N}_0 \) ) so if a number is a natural number it must be a whole number.
This is true.
3. Whole numbers \( {0;1;2;3;\ldots} \) only go up in steps of 1, so there cannot be any decimal numbers in the whole numbers, making this true.
Therefore \( (2) \) and \( (3) \) is true.

af.latex:
Beskou elke stelling noukeurig:
1. Daar is heelgetalle wat nie in dieselfde kategorie as natuurlike getalle val nie (alle negatiewe getalle), daarom is dit onwaar.
2. Die natuurlike getalle is \( {1;2;3;\ldots} \) en telgetalle is \( {0;1;2;3;\ldots} \) (die sirkel \( \mathbb{N} \) is binne \( \mathbb{N}_0 \) ) so as 'n getal 'n natuurlike getal is, moet dit 'n telgetal ook wees. Daarom is dit waar.
3. Telgetalle \( {0;1;2;3;\ldots} \) gaan slegs in tellings van \( 1 \) op, so daarom kan daar nie desimale getalle in telgetalle wees nie, wat hierdie stelling waar maak.
Daarom is stellings \( (2) \) en \( (3) \) waar.

en.latex:
The number does not terminate (this is shown by the \( \ldots \) ). There is also no indication of a repeating pattern of digits since there is no dot or bar over any of the numbers.The next three digits could be any numbers.
Note that while it looks like there is a pattern in the digits we do not know if this pattern continues on.
Irrational, there is no repeating pattern.

Irrasionaal, omdat daar geen herhalende patroon is nie.
